						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājakēsarivarman</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Tribhº Kulōttuṅgachōḷadēva I: Year 49 = 1118-19 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This incomplete inscription contains the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> of the king commencing with <hi rend="italic">Pugaḷmādu viḷaṅga,</hi> etc. </p>						

						<p>It refers to the sale of land by the <hi rend="italic">ūrār</hi> of Śēmam-Āṟṟūr in Tirumuṉaippāḍi Empēṟṟūr-nāḍu in Gaṅgaikoṇḍaśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu. Also refers to the festival in the month of Vaikāśi of the god Tiruppulippagavar in Śiṟṟiṅgūr, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēyam</hi> in Kuṟukkaik-kūṟṟam in Malāḍu <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Jananātha-vaḷanāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
